  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and involves multiple levels of legislation and regulation:\n\n1. International Level\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group standards\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Mandatory reporting of large transactions\n- Financial institution compliance obligations\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial crime enforcement agencies\n- Central banks\n- Treasury departments\n- Law enforcement organizations\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Internal control mechanisms\n\n6. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Civil penalties\n- Financial sanctions\n- International cooperation\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes by establishing comprehensive regulatory standards and enforcement protocols.",
